---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of service for Novalink Technologies covering scope, responsibilities, commercial terms, and legal framing."
>
  <section class="container-shell pt-14">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm text-slate-600">
      These terms describe how Novalink Technologies provides services and how project engagements are handled.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container-shell pt-12">
    <div class="panel space-y-4 p-6 text-sm text-slate-600">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">1. Scope of Services</h2>
      <p>Novalink provides scoped services across websites, landing pages, workflow automation, integrations, commerce/payment enablement, and search/acquisition support.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">2. Proposals, Fees, and Timelines</h2>
      <p>Specific deliverables, fees, timelines, and dependencies are defined in proposals, quotations, or signed agreements. Those documents govern each engagement.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">3. Client Responsibilities</h2>
      <p>Clients are responsible for providing timely information, approvals, access credentials, and required third-party account permissions needed for implementation.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">4. Content and Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>Clients retain ownership of their business content and brand assets. Reusable frameworks, internal methods, and pre-existing Novalink materials remain Novalink intellectual property unless otherwise agreed in writing.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">5. Service Boundaries and Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>Novalink provides practical implementation support and does not guarantee specific commercial results. Outcomes depend on client operations, market conditions, and execution decisions outside Novalink control.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>To the fullest extent allowed by applicable law, Novalink is not liable for indirect or consequential losses. Total liability is limited to fees paid for the specific scoped service giving rise to the claim.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">7. Governing Law and Contact</h2>
      <p>These terms are governed by the laws of Malaysia unless otherwise agreed in a signed contract. For legal or commercial clarifications, contact <a class="font-medium text-brand-800" href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>{siteConfig.email}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
